annotationA: Ras-related GTP binding A/B (RagA-B) is a Ras family GTPase that forms a heterodimer with RagC-D.  The heterodimer localizes on the lysosome surface and functions to relay amino acid signals to Tor activation by recruiting it to the lysosome
annotationB: Alicorn, isoform A; AMP-activated protein kinase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: cellular response to DNA damage stimulus; maintenance of apical/basal cell polarity; neuron cellular homeostasis
